  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nIf we configure any parameter to be `Infinity` value that is parsed as `NaN` while running the node. \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nThe `Infinity` values should be parsed as `Infinity`. \r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. Create a configuration file with following; \r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst rcConfig = ({\r\n      network: \"dev\",\r\n      preset: \"minimal\",\r\n      dataDir: rootDir,\r\n      rest: true,\r\n      \"rest.address\": this.address,\r\n      \"rest.port\": this.restPort,\r\n      \"network.allowPublishToZeroPeers\": true,\r\n      eth1: false,\r\n      listenAddress: this.address,\r\n      port: this.port,\r\n      metrics: false,\r\n      dev: true,\r\n      \"params.ALTAIR_FORK_EPOCH\": String(Infinity),\r\n      \"params.BELLATRIX_FORK_EPOCH\": String(Infinity),\r\n    } as unknown) as IBeaconArgs & IGlobalArgs;\r\n```\r\n2. Save it as a file \r\n```ts\r\nawait writeFile(`${rootDir}/rc_config.json`, JSON.stringify(rcConfig, null, 2));\r\n```\r\n3. Start the node with it. \r\n```\r\n./packages/cli/bin/lodestar.js beacon --rcConfig `${this.rootDir}/rc_config.json`\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n\r\nBecause of the following mis-configuration node get following errors: \r\n\r\n```\r\nSep-01 12:40:20.005[API]             error: Req req-2e getSyncCommitteeDuties error  Empty SyncCommitteeCache\r\nError: Empty SyncCommitteeCache\r\n    at SyncCommitteeCacheEmpty.get validatorIndexMap [as validatorIndexMap] (file:////lodestar/packages/state-transition/src/cache/syncCommitteeCache.ts:27:11)\r\n    at Object.getSyncCommitteeDuties (file:///lodestar/packages/beacon-node/src/api/impl/validator/index.ts:427:64)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n\r\n- OS: Mac\r\n- Version: 13.0\r\n- Branch: [unstable]\r\n- Commit hash: [04030be455d111fdf85838fb59235cd197d65154]\r\n",
